https://youtu.be/cOIBRr9fsdM
https://youtu.be/YEDXBmMv5zE
For anyone whom says that they love the Lord Jesus Christ, it serves well to do some research behind everything that you do, and to be weary of anything that the world deems okay and celebrates. He calls us to be set apart and a light in this world.

“You are the salt of the earth. But if the salt should lose its taste, how can it be made salty? It’s no longer good for anything but to be thrown out and trampled on by men.  “You are the light of the world. A city situated on a hill cannot be hidden.  No one lights a lamp and puts it under a basket,   but rather on a lampstand, and it gives light for all who are in the house.  In the same way, let your light shine   before men, so that they may see your good works and give glory to your Father in heaven.
Matthew 5:13‭-‬16

There are dark origins and history behind this digusting holiday that have absolutely nothing to do with Christ. He wasn't even born on December 25th. He was born sometime around the feast of tabernacles which varies from late September to October. That in itself is beautiful the way that the Lord orchestrated that because the Word became flesh and tabernacled among us. And yet we do not acknowledge Him as we should for the gift of His Son.

And the Word became flesh and tabernacled among us. We looked upon His glory, the glory of the one and only from the Father, full of grace and truth. John 1:14

December 25th is when the Romans thought the winter solstice took place and the birth of their Pagan Sun god Mithra was. The devil has been a liar from the beginning and he has deceived so many into believing that they are worshipping Christ when they take part in these satanic rituals disguised behind lights and trees and Santa.
But the Word of God is clear!!!

Do not worship the LORD your God in the way these pagan peoples worship their gods. Deuteronomy 12:4

There are so many other references in the Word that tell us that God does not want to be worshipped in such ways. You may not be actually passing your children through the fire to worship molech as the Israelites did back then, but when you set your children on Santa's lap and lie to them for years about a fat man that does all these different "magical" things you DESTORY their trust in you and weaken their faith. How can they trust anything their parents say or any other adult that has lied to them so easily and continuously. And for what exactly?!?!? So they can have fun. There are many other ways to have fun and create wonderful memories with your children and family without lying to them.

Beware lest any man spoil you through philosophy and vain deceit, after the tradition of men, after the rudiments of the world, and not after Christ. Colossians 2:8

I say all this in love, because I used to be an avid holiday celebrator too until the Lord gave me discernment and wisdom. He will give it to you as well if you'll only ask.

For the LORD gives wisdom; from his mouth come knowledge and understanding. Proverbs 2:6

Because strait is the gate, and narrow is the way, which leadeth unto life, and few there be that find it. Matthew 7:14

“Not everyone who says to Me, ‘Lord, Lord! ’ will enter the kingdom of heaven, but only the one who does the will of My Father in heaven.  On that day many will say to Me, ‘Lord, Lord, didn’t we prophesy in Your name, drive out demons in Your name, and do many miracles in Your name? ’  Then I will announce to them, ‘I never knew you! Depart from Me, you lawbreakers!’
Matthew 7:21‭-‬23

For anyone whom says that they love the Lord Jesus Christ, it serves well to do some research behind everything that you do, and to be weary of anything that the world deems okay and celebrates. He calls us to be set apart and a light in this world.

“You are the salt of the earth. But if the salt should lose its taste, how can it be made salty? It’s no longer good for anything but to be thrown out and trampled on by men.  “You are the light of the world. A city situated on a hill cannot be hidden.  No one lights a lamp and puts it under a basket,   but rather on a lampstand, and it gives light for all who are in the house.  In the same way, let your light shine   before men, so that they may see your good works and give glory to your Father in heaven.
Matthew 5:13‭-‬16

There are dark origins and history behind this digusting holiday that have absolutely nothing to do with Christ. He wasn't even born on December 25th. He was born sometime around the feast of tabernacles which varies from late September to October. That in itself is beautiful the way that the Lord orchestrated that because the Word became flesh and tabernacled among us. And yet we do not acknowledge Him as we should for the gift of His Son.

And the Word became flesh and tabernacled among us. We looked upon His glory, the glory of the one and only from the Father, full of grace and truth. John 1:14

 December 25th is when the Romans thought the winter solstice took place and the birth of their Pagan Sun god Mithra was. The devil has been a liar from the beginning and he has deceived so many into believing that they are worshipping Christ when they take part in these satanic rituals disguised behind lights and trees and Santa. 
But the Word of God is clear!!! 

Do not worship the LORD your God in the way these pagan peoples worship their gods. Deuteronomy 12:4

 There are so many other references in the Word that tell us that God does not want to be worshipped in such ways. You may not be actually passing your children through the fire to worship molech as the Israelites did back then, but when you set your children on Santa's lap and lie to them for years about a fat man that does all these different "magical" things you DESTORY their trust in you and weaken their faith. How can they trust anything their parents say or any other adult that has lied to them so easily and continuously. And for what exactly?!?!? So they can have fun. There are many other ways to have fun and create wonderful memories with your children and family without lying to them. 

Beware lest any man spoil you through philosophy and vain deceit, after the tradition of men, after the rudiments of the world, and not after Christ. Colossians 2:8

I say all this in love, because I used to be an avid holiday celebrator too until the Lord gave me discernment and wisdom. He will give it to you as well if you'll only ask. 

For the LORD gives wisdom; from his mouth come knowledge and understanding. Proverbs 2:6

Because strait is the gate, and narrow is the way, which leadeth unto life, and few there be that find it. Matthew 7:14

“Not everyone who says to Me, ‘Lord, Lord! ’ will enter the kingdom of heaven, but only the one who does the will of My Father in heaven.  On that day many will say to Me, ‘Lord, Lord, didn’t we prophesy in Your name, drive out demons in Your name, and do many miracles in Your name? ’  Then I will announce to them, ‘I never knew you! Depart from Me, you lawbreakers!’
Matthew 7:21‭-‬23

Jesus said in John 14:15 “If you love Me, you will keep My commands."

It's time to educate ourselves and stand firm for the Truth! If you say you love Christ show Him and allow yourself to be led by Him and not this world. 

I love you all and God bless.
